    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-05-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-05-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="51" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d51">
                <head>No. 51.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Logan</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-05-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 24,
                            1883</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Logan says that Iglesias has signed the treaty according to the bases
                        already announced. Chili will yield the north of Peru at once, and keep an
                        army in the center. Montero remains in possession of the south only. Peace
                        will follow if the United States Government recognizes Iglesias. If this is
                        not done, however, serious complications will ensue and peace will certainly
                        be postponed.</p>
            </div>
